# MAXEK Construction ERP Rules

Development constraints for all Cursor work on MAXEK Construction ERP. Follow these rules on every task.

## Development rules

1. **Do NOT redesign any UI.** The existing UI reflects approved workflows and user training.
2. **Do NOT rename modules.** Module names map to navigation, permissions, URLs, and documentation.
3. **Do NOT remove existing features.** Features may support edge cases (retention, variations, multi-site payroll).
4. **Fix backend before frontend.** Stabilize routes, queries, and business logic first.
5. **Reuse existing templates.** New pages should extend the same base templates.
6. **Reuse common CRUD components.** List, form, filter, and pagination patterns already exist.
7. **Reuse common toolbar.** Toolbar actions (save, export, print, back) use shared handlers.
8. **Every button must have a working backend route.** Wire each action to a real endpoint.
9. **Every route must return valid data.** Validate shape, status codes, and edge cases.
10. **Every fix must be tested before commit.** Exercise the changed flow manually or with tests.
11. **Commit after every completed task.** Small, focused commits preserve rollback points.
12. **Never modify unrelated modules.** Change only files required for the stated task.

Full rationale: `docs/MAXEK_ERP_RULES.md`

## Definition of Done (every module)

A module is complete **only** when all of the following pass in browser testing. See `docs/MODULE_DEFINITION_OF_DONE.md` for verification steps and sign-off template.

1. Dashboard opens
2. Module opens
3. New works
4. Save works
5. Open works
6. View works
7. Edit works
8. Delete works
9. Search works
10. Status filter works
11. Date filter works
12. Sort works
13. Refresh works
14. Export Excel works
15. Export PDF works
16. Print works
17. Run Report works
18. No 404 errors
19. No 500 errors
20. No JavaScript console errors

**Policy:** No module task is done until all 20 items pass. Partial CRUD without export/report/error checks does not count as complete.
